java.io.Serializable, org.mozilla.javascript.debug.DebuggableObject, org.mozilla.javascript.IdFunctionCall, org.mozilla.javascript.Scriptable
public class GlobalScope
extends org.mozilla.javascript.ImporterTopLevel

Top-level scope object for RhinoServlet. This defines the standard objects, a global static "Rhino" object that gives access for controlling RhinoServlet. It also adds a self-pointing global property "global", and makes Rhino.require a protected global variable.

Marcello

Method Detail

getModuleScope

public org.mozilla.javascript.Scriptable getModuleScope(java.lang.String name)
Each module has its own scope from which its scripts are executed. This method returns that scope (creating it if necessary). It also creates the necessary object hierarchy. For example, if this method were called with the argument "module1.module2.Script", a global.module1 would be created, and within that a module2, global.module1.module2.

Parameters:
name - the module/script name (or .*)
Returns:
the scope associated with this module/script name
